message:
Brian,

I did not see any contact information on your profile. We need to connect to make sure you have not already been submitted to some of my clients, to see if you are interested in these clients (project/location wise), etc. That is information that I submit to the client and that is the only way they get your information to then make a decision if they would like to interview you or not.

>On September 19, 2015, 9:46 AM, Brian Cullinan wrote:
>All of my resume information is available through my linked in profile. If your clients are interested in an in person interview we can go from there.
> 
> On Fri September 18 2015, Daniel Faulkner wrote:
> 
> Brian,
> 
> Thank you for the reply. Do you have a phone number I can reach you at?
> 
> >On September 17, 2015, 10:42 PM, Brian Cullinan wrote:
> >Thank you for your interest, 
> > 
> > I have been developing software since I was only 11 years old. I started in VB4 and explored .Net since it's inception. Later I honed my skills on the web with PHP and JavaScript. I enjoy all forms of software development and computer administration. In previous positions a 6 month salary review has worked well, as it gives us both a chance to show what we are made of, without breaking the bank. I have a lot of experience with start-ups, so I am no stranger to bringing new products and technologies to market in a controlled environment. I would enjoy a change to meet more of the team. For reference, I would be looking in the ballpark of $180k. Thank you. 
> > 
> > -Brian 
> > 
> > On 9/16/15 6:55 PM, Daniel Faulkner wrote: 
> > --------------------
> > Hi Brian, 
> > 
> > My name is Daniel and I am a Senior Technical Recruiter with Productive Data Solutions in Tempe, AZ. I wanted to reach out to you based on your current background and see if you were looking for any career opportunities at this time. If so, I have a couple of positions available that I think you could be a good fit for. If you are interested in speaking about them in more detail, please feel free to reach out. I appreciate your time and consideration.
> > 
> > Thanks,
> > 
> > Daniel Faulkner
